A magistrate has summoned the Embu Police Station OCS to explain why a suspect was not presented to court within 24 hours.  Elvis Fundi complained that he was held at the court cells the whole day on Monday and was not presented before a magistrate.  He allegedly hit a reveler with a beer bottle at the Lexo Bar and Restaurant in Embu town.  At the same court, a woman accused police of denying her the right to see her baby for two days.  Caroline Murugi faces charges of malicious damage to property in Kagumoni, Gaturi, Embu County.  70-year-old stabs wife to death in Sh6,000 dispute  Embu ready to host KICOSCA Games next week  Embu OCS summoned for holding suspect beyond 24 hours  70-year-old man to be arraigned for stabbing wife to death  Utata wa Ardhi Embu: Viongozi walaani ubomoaji huku maelfu wakiachwa bila makao  Nabbed for Sodomy: Police in Embu hold paedophile suspect after he allegedly defiled nephew aged 12  BBI in Embu County: Bill subjected to public participation, 3 counties have approved and 1 declined By Boniface Gikandi | 7 hours ago By Muriithi Mugo | 7 hours ago By Kipsang Joseph | 10 hours ago By Boniface Gikandi | 1 day ago